    • coalesce

      @SafeVarargs public static <T> T coalesce(T... items)

      Returns the first non-null given parameter, if any are given.

      Emulates: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Operators/Nullish_coalescing_operator

      Type Parameters:
      T - Any non-primitive type.
      Parameters:
      items - The list of parameters to find a non-null value from.
      Returns:
      Returns the first non-null value found, or null.

    • chain

      public static <T> T chain(NullCoalescing.NullChecker<T> statement)

      Allows developers to chain statements that might otherwise require a ton of null checking.

      Emulates: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Operators/Optional_chaining

      Type Parameters:
      T - Any non-primitive type.
      Parameters:
      statement - Function that throws an exception to call the chained statement within.
      Returns:
      Returns the result of the chained statement, or null if the chain failed.

    • chain

      public static <T> T chain(NullCoalescing.NullChecker<T> statement, T fallback)

      Allows developers to chain statements that might otherwise require a ton of null checking.

      Emulates: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Operators/Optional_chaining and https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Operators/Nullish_coalescing_operator

      Type Parameters:
      T - Any non-primitive type.
      Parameters:
      statement - Function that throws an exception to call the chained statement within.
      fallback - The value that will be fallen back upon if something goes wrong.
      Returns:
      Returns the result of the chained statement, or the fallback if the chain failed.
